subSubSection.paragraph:
Cirrhilabrus rubrisquamis
Randall & Emery, 1983: 21; fig. 1 (description); 
Winterbottom et al. 1989
: 53; pl VII-E (checklist, fishes of the Chagos Archipelago); 
Winterbottom and Anderson 1997
: 15 (revised checklist, fishes of the Chagos Archipelago)

Based on color photograph of holotype when fresh (Fig. 
1
): head yellow, brownish posteriorly; lower part of head whitish to pale pink; preopercle prominently purple on outer edge; iris yellow; body orangey pink, fading to whitish pink ventrally; body with a network of dark purple scales arranged in a chain link pattern from just after dorsal fin origin to edge of caudal peduncle, absent from lower third of body; dorsal fin hyaline, yellow on distal half; posterior dorsal fin yellowish hyaline with metallic blue spots; caudal fin bluish hyaline with yellow and blue vermiculation, often broken in spots; anal fin similar to dorsal fin; pelvic fins hyaline; pectoral fin base with a purple band; pectoral fins pinkish hyaline.
